  fishName: Giant Grouper
  scientificName: Epinephelus lanceolatus
  description: Also known as 'Lapu-lapu' in the Philippines. One of the largest reef
    fish, can grow over 2.5 meters and weigh 400 kg.
  status: 0
  iucnStatus: Vulnerable
  populationTrend: Decreasing
  habitat: Coral reefs, rocky areas, and lagoons in tropical and subtropical waters
  distribution: Indo-Pacific region including Philippines, from Red Sea to Australia
    and Japan
  threats: Overfishing for live fish trade, habitat destruction of coral reefs, slow
    growth and late maturity, bycatch
  importance: Top predator on coral reefs, maintains reef ecosystem balance, culturally
    significant in Philippines, important for reef health
  conservationEfforts: Marine protected areas, size and catch limits, reef conservation
    programs, aquaculture research, fishing regulations
